text: A Más (formerly: a+) is a Mexican television network owned by TV Azteca, was released on March 20, 2017 in three cities and later expanded in April 7, 2017. The channel is listed on frequency 7.2 from Azteca 7 transmitters and was originally released for regional programming. == References == Category:Television networks Category:2017 establishments in North America
title: A Más
